<TITLE> Body found, 3 arrested over housewife's murder </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, July 3 (bdnews24.com)Police recovered a young man's body and arrested three people on charges of the murder of a housewife at Uttara in the capital on Friday. Sub-inspector of Uttara Police Station Faruq Hossain said that body was identified as that of Nurul Islam Rana, 19, a reporter of 'Muktamon' from the identity card in his pocket. The body was found behind the RMC Hospital at Uttara. Rana had no sign of injuries in the body and police were waiting for the autopsy report, he added. In the other incident, husband Touhidul Alam Rony and his brothers have been charged with strangling Afroza Parveen Julie, 24. The brothers are Shafiul Alam and Rafiqul alam. Her mother Papiya Begum pressed the murder charges with Uttara Police Station. Uttara police sub-inspector Mohammad Shafiq said Julie was strangulated on Thursday night. Her husband and relatives took her to the hospital. Police said her relatives killed her due to a family feud. 
